[0.001, "o", "/home/fat/web/docs/php/test_mem.php\u001b[7;3H  last request cpu:     0.00\u001b[8;3H  last request memory:  0\u001b[K\u001b[9;3H\u001b[K\u001b[10dNote: There is a real-time FPM status monitoring sample web page available\u001b[11;3H      It's available in: /usr/share/php/fpm/status.html\u001b[12;3H\u001b[K\u001b[13dNote: The value must start with a leading slash (/). The value can be\u001b[14;3H      anything, but it may not be a good idea to use the .php extension or it\u001b[15;3H      may conflict with a real PHP file.\u001b[16;3HDefault Value: not set\u001b[K\r\u001b[17d;pm.status_path = /status\u001b[K\r\u001b[18d\u001b[K\u001b[19d; The address on which to accept FastCGI status request. This creates a new\r\u001b[20d; invisible pool that can handle requests independently. This is useful\r\u001b[21d; if the main pool is busy with long running requests because it is still possible\r\u001b[22d; to get the status before finishing the long running requests.\u001b[23;3H\u001b[K\r\u001b[32d; Default Value: value of the listen option\r\u001b[33d;pm.status_\u001b[30m\u001b[43mlisten = \u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f127.0.0.1:9001\r\u001b[35d; The ping URI to call the monitoring page of FPM. If this value is not set, no\r\u001b[36d; URI will be recognized as a ping page. This could be used to test from outside\r\u001b[37d; that FPM is alive and responding, or to\r\u001b[38d; - create a graph of FPM availability (rrd or such);\r\u001b[39d; - remove a server from a group if it is not responding (load balancing);\r\u001b[40d; - trigger alerts for the operating team (24/7).\u001b[41;11He value must start with a leading slash (/). The value can be\r\u001b[42d;       anything, but it may not be a good idea to use the .php extension or it\r\u001b[43d;\u001b[9Gmay conflict with a real PHP file.\u001b[44;3HDefault Value: not set\r\u001b[45d;ping.path = /ping\u001b[K\r\u001b[46d\u001b[K\u001b[47d; This directive may be used to customize the response of a ping request. The\u001b[48;3Hresponse is formatted as text/plain with a 200 response code.\u001b[K\u001b[49;3HDefault Value: pong\u001b[K\r\u001b[50d;ping.response = pong\u001b[K\r\u001b[51d\u001b[K\u001b[52d; "]
[0.001, "o", "The access log file\u001b[K\u001b[53;3HDefault: not set\u001b[K\r\u001b[54d;access.log = log/$pool.access.log\r\u001b[55d\u001b[K\u001b[56d; The access log format.\r\u001b[57d; The following syntax is allowed\u001b[58;3H %%: the '%' character\u001b[K\u001b[59;3H %C: %CPU used by the request\u001b[K\u001b[60;3H     it can accept the following format:\u001b[K\r\u001b[61d;      - %{user}C for user CPU only\r\u001b[62d;      - %{system}C for system CPU only\r\u001b[63d;\u001b[8G- %{total}C  for user + system CPU (default)\u001b[64;3H %d: time taken to serve the request\u001b[K\u001b[33;12H"]
