[0.000, "o", "Define the anonymous ftp password (your email address). PHP's default setting\r\u001b[6d; for this is empty.\u001b[7;3Hhttps://php.net/from\u001b[K\r\u001b[8d;from=\"john@doe.com\"\u001b[K\u001b[10;3HDefine the User-Agent string. PHP's default setting for this is empty.\u001b[K\u001b[11;3Hhttps://php.net/user-agent\u001b[K\r\u001b[12d;user_agent=\"PHP\"\u001b[K\r\u001b[13d\u001b[K\u001b[14d; Default timeout for socket based streams (seconds)\u001b[15;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "https://php.net/default-socket-timeout\u001b[K\r\u001b[16d"]
[0.000, "o", "default_socket_timeout = 60\u001b[K\r\u001b[17d\u001b[K\u001b[18d; If your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[K\u001b[19;3Hor you are running on a Mac and need to deal with files from\u001b[20;3Hunix or win32 systems, setting this flag will cause PHP to\u001b[21;3Hautomatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\r\u001b[22d; fgets() and file() will work regardless of the source of the file.\u001b[23;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-detect-line-endings\u001b[K\r\u001b[24d;auto_detect_line_endings = Off\u001b[K\r\u001b[25d\u001b[K\u001b[26d;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\u001b[27d; Dynamic Extensions ;\r\u001b[28d;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\u001b[29d\u001b[K\u001b[30d; If you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\u001b[31;3Hsyntax:\u001b[K\u001b[32;3H\u001b[K\u001b[33d  \u001b[30m\u001b[43mextension=\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000fmodulename\u001b[K\u001b[34;3H\u001b[K\u001b[35dFor example:\u001b[K\r\u001b[36d;\u001b[37d   extension=mysqli\u001b[K\u001b[38;3H\u001b[K\u001b[39dWhen the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[40;3Hdirectory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[K\u001b[41;3H\u001b[K\u001b[42d  extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[K\r\u001b[43d;\u001b[44d Note : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\u001b[K\u001b[45;3H'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\u001b[K\u001b[46;3Hdeprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\u001b[47;3Hmove to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax."]
